    <item>
      <title>14.06 Dining Hall</title>
      <link>https://shikarito.wordpress.com/kusuriya-no-hitorigoto/14-06-dining-hall/</link>
      <guid isPermaLink="true">https://shikarito.wordpress.com/kusuriya-no-hitorigoto/14-06-dining-hall/</guid>
      <pubDate>Sat, 16 Nov 2024 10:19:21 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;main class="wp-block-group is-layout-flow wp-block-group-is-layout-flow"&gt; &lt;div class="wp-block-group is-layout-constrained wp-block-group-is-layout-constrained"&gt;&lt;h1 class="wp-block-post-title"&gt;14.06 Dining Hall&lt;/h1&gt;   &lt;div style="height:1px" aria-hidden="true" class="wp-block-spacer"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;/div&gt;   &lt;div class="entry-content wp-block-post-content is-layout-constrained wp-block-post-content-is-layout-constrained"&gt; &lt;p&gt;(&lt;a href="https://shikarito.wordpress.com/kusuriya-no-hitorigoto/14-05-the-interview/"&gt;Previous Chapter&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Friend’s discount. Kokuyou priced his research materials at ten silvers for her.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;While Maomao would have preferred a bigger discount, the high-ranking court physicians had paid fifty silvers for it. As it was not good to be too greedy, she held back. She also wanted to stay on good terms with Kokuyou for a little while longer.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;She had the option of getting the high-ranking court physicians show her what they copied as well, but she wanted to review the original text Kokuyou wrote as soon as possible.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Kokuyou may be particular about money, but he wasn’t a miser. It was just that he used money as an easy way to gauge how people appraised him.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;The man had a flippant way of speaking, but he was able to think about medicine in a deeply rational way as well. Even though he made concessions for others, he would often suddenly disappear if they continued to make unfair bargains.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;It didn’t mean that people like Kokuyou who were benevolent to those who treated them badly were kind. He could only do so because he had little attachment to people. She had to bear that fact in mind.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;As Maomao read through the copy of Kokuyou’s materials, she nodded in approval. The materials were with her now that the high-ranking court physicians had finished copying it. She was reading it in the dining hall, not in her room since it was much brighter and warmer here. Ten silvers was a great expense, so she wanted to save on oil and charcoal for lighting and heating.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Maomao, what is this?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Changsha came over to look.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;I want to ask for a reading fee.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;But the junior court lady’s salary was much lower than Maomao’s. Since Changsha cooked more often, Maomao decided to let her see it.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“It’s research material on epidemics. This might prove useful from now on, so shall we read through it together?” Maomao said.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Are you sure?” Changsha’s face brightened. What an honest child.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;She’s different from the girls who come to the pleasure district.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;All the girls who come to the pleasure district have been sold. They came from poor peasant families or were the daughters of merchants who have suddenly fallen into hard times. &lt;em&gt;So it is natural for them to be bitter,&lt;/em&gt; Maomao thought. Although girls with nice personalities do exist as well, they don’t last long without good common sense.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;It didn’t mean that the girls who become courtesans have nasty personalities—it was a comparison to show how blessed Changsha was.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Kokuyou’s handwriting was surprisingly good. There were scribbles in a foreign script in various places as well.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Seeing these makes me want to see the original text.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;She heard that Kokuyou’s master was a foreigner, so she figured that Kokuyou’s medicinal vocabulary was mixed with foreign language.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Smallpox, huh? Will Yo be alright?” Changsha said.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“It is what it is. Concern won’t do much, so let us do what we can.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“You’re right. Come to think of it,” Changsha looked a little frustrated. She brought up a different topic for a change of mood. “I want to say that Yao-san and En’en-san are the same, but…”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“But?” Maomao asked.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“I found it unusual that she had an argument with En’en-san the other day.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“An argument?” Maomao had an idea what the argument was about. “Could it be about a man?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Yes. Yao-san is a really awkward person, right?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Ah, you can tell?” Maomao found herself agreeing with Changsha.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Yes. Yao-san likes a person called Rahan, right?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;She was so accurate Maomao felt bad for Yao. &lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Likes, might not be right term for it, but well. Rather, you even know his name, huh?” Maomao had no idea if Yao was aware of her feeling yet.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Yes. En’en-san is always letting it slip. While she has a face of a demon. Also, I have pretty much grasped it from the hints the two of them were dropping. How audacious, right? To come up with a reason to settle into the house of the person you like. The topic of the argument was about whether it’s time they should move out.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Maomao nodded in understanding.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Also, En’en-san only has eyes for Yao-san. The person that comes over to see En’en-san from time to time gets mercilessly cut off too.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Uh huh.” Rahan’s older brother’s face came to mind. His real name was Kan-something-san.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Yao-san is awkward as well. Is the target of her feelings someone who would sprout love from having her getting close to him by staying at his residence? I think normally, he would find them noisy and annoying. Well, Yao-san is from a good family. She&amp;#8217;s wealthy. She&amp;#8217;s attractive too. So, it would only be enviable for those from the unrelated male camp. The person concerned would find it utterly unbearable.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;No, honest child, repeal that.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;The honest child had observed the bad points of her seniors and spoke frankly about it. Given how she passed the exam, she was a smart child.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Will you say this before the people in question?” Maomao asked.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“There’s no way I can.” Changsha shook her head. “But for the both of them, I don’t think this will end unless they give up and express their feelings or they come to their senses. It would be good to have a third party come in, but it would be difficult since Yao-san is stubborn.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Maomao was also of the same mind.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“En’en-san has no way of telling Yao-san directly, and even if she did, she would be shrugged off. She can only indirectly argue with her with talks of moving out.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;It probably wasn’t a real argument. En’en had to be fully feeling regretful towards Yao.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“There &lt;em&gt;is &lt;/em&gt;one other way to resolve it, but it has the lowest chance of happening.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Ahh, would it be for the other party to like her too?” Maomao asked.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Yes.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;No&lt;/em&gt;&lt;em&gt;t in a million years&lt;/em&gt;&lt;em&gt;, &lt;/em&gt;Maomao shook her head.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“But it is possible that Rahan person could give in, right?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“She comes with a very scary sister-in-law called En’en, though?” Maomao said.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“That is a terrifying thought.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;There were barely any people left in the dining hall whilst they were chatting. The dorm manager was imploring them to leave with her eyes.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Well then, shall we get ready for bed?” Maomao asked.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Yes.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Maomao got up from her seat and picked up the research materials.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;And that was when she became aware of the characteristic sound of footsteps approaching.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Good daaaay.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;To end her speech in such a characteristic way, it could only be Chue.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“It’s not the time for &lt;em&gt;good day&lt;/em&gt; anymore. The sun has already set.” Maomao sensed trouble in the air. “Changsha, please head to bed. You have an early start tomorrow too, right?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Excuse me.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Although Changsha was curious, Maomao headed to work. “Now then, what could today’s matter be about? Are we going to watch Basen-sama again? Wouldn’t that be considered voyeurism at this time of the day? More importantly, I doubt Basen-sama has the finesse to ask girls out in the middle of the night.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Yes. Chue-san won’t have to work so hard if my brother-in-law can sneak into a woman’s bedroom or arrange for a tryst. Shall we take him to the Verdigris Mansion for practice again?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Absolutely not. The madam will beat me up if he struggled and destroyed the building.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Also, she had no idea how high the madam would overcharge in the reparations bill.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“How unfortunate. Today’s matter is not about my brother-in-law. A slight problem came up, so won&amp;#8217;t you come to the Moon Prince’s place today?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“May I ask what this problem is?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Jinshi had been summoning Maomao less often for matters like this. He no longer had to excuse to have her come in for wound treatment, and he must be busy with work as well. But would the biggest reason be that the person himself was drawing a line?&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;And so, Maomao presumed that he had summoned her for a proper reason this time.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;There were no other court ladies in the dining hall. The dorm manager, perhaps having read the room, had stepped outside.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Chue leaned towards Maomao’s ear. “A cursed jar has been found under the eaves of a certain government official’s house.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Oh my, what a nostalgic matter.” It was a matter Maomao heard all the time back when she was at the inner palace.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“And a troubling point is how that the government official’s daughter is getting weaker.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;To the point that the matter would be brought to Jinshi. She guessed that they had to be quite a high-ranking family even though they were calling them a government official.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“You mean to break the curse.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Yes, just as Maomao-san says.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“I do not believe in curses?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Fufufu, that is your feelings. Even if curses don’t exist for Maomao-san, for other people, they can only call things they can’t explain a curse.”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Reasonable&lt;/em&gt;, Maomao thought as well. “Is there a possibility of there being poison?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Chue was all smiles. “Won’t you come with meee?”&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;“Can’t be helped,” Maomao said, although she didn’t look displeased at all.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;It’s a bad side of me&lt;/em&gt;, she thought, but it was an unchangeable part of Maomao’s nature.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity" /&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;sub&gt;T/N: Since it&amp;#8217;s been so long, I forgot how I usually translated Rokushoukan, or if I did at all, so I&amp;#8217;m going with my personal pick for the translation this time&amp;#8230;&lt;/sub&gt;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p class="has-text-align-right"&gt;(&lt;a href="https://shikarito.wordpress.com/kusuriya-no-hitorigoto/14-07-the-cursed-jar-1/"&gt;Next Chapter&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;div id="jp-post-flair" class="sharedaddy sd-like-enabled"&gt;&lt;div class="sharedaddy sd-sharing-enabled"&gt;&lt;div class="robots-nocontent sd-block sd-social sd-social-official sd-sharing"&gt;&lt;h3 class="sd-title"&gt;Share this:&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;div class="sd-content"&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li class="share-facebook"&gt;&lt;div class="fb-share-button" data-href="https://shikarito.wordpress.com/kusuriya-no-hitorigoto/14-06-dining-hall/" data-layout="button_count"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li class="share-end"&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class='sharedaddy sd-block sd-like jetpack-likes-widget-wrapper jetpack-likes-widget-unloaded' id='like-post-wrapper-130534757-5027-691898f35614f' data-src='//widgets.wp.com/likes/index.html?ver=20251115#blog_id=130534757&amp;amp;post_id=5027&amp;amp;origin=shikarito.wordpress.com&amp;amp;obj_id=130534757-5027-691898f35614f' data-name='like-post-frame-130534757-5027-691898f35614f' data-title='Like or Reblog'&gt;&lt;div class='likes-widget-placeholder post-likes-widget-placeholder' style='height: 55px;'&gt;&lt;span class='button'&gt;&lt;span&gt;Like&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class='loading'&gt;Loading&amp;#8230;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;span class='sd-text-color'&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;a class='sd-link-color' href="https://shikarito.wordpress.com/kusuriya-no-hitorigoto/14-06-dining-hall/"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/main&gt;</description>
